Alternate Data streams is an NTFS file attribute and was designed to provide compatibility with the MAcOS HFS

2 different forks/streams
1.Data stream - it contains the data of the file
2.Resource Stream - it contains metadata of the file

Attackers can use ADs to hide the malicious code.
This can be done by storing the malicious code or exe 

Alternate Data Streams is not an NTFS and ext4 filesystem attribute.
